            <section id="grammar" class="mb-10">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-4">Grammar Focus ü©∫</h2>
                <div class="bg-stone-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-stone-200 dark:border-gray-700 mb-6">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-stone-800 dark:text-stone-200">'To feel' + Adjective</h3>
                    <p class="mb-4 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Use the verb **feel** to describe your state or condition.</p>
                    <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
                        <li>I **feel good**.</li>
                        <li>She **feels sick**.</li>
                        <li>They **feel tired**.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-stone-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-stone-200 dark:border-gray-700">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-stone-800 dark:text-stone-200">'To have' + Noun (Ailment)</h3>
                    <p class="mb-4 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Use the verb **have** to say what problem you have.</p>
                     <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
                        <li>I **have a** headache.</li>
                        <li>He **has a** sore throat.</li>
                        <li>We **have** colds.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </section>
            <hr class="my-10 border-stone-200 dark:border-gray-700">

